cs.CR, cs.LO, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with analyzing cryptographic protocols for the property of secrecy, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
2. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) - The paper presents a new formal method to analyze protocols, which involves logical reasoning and inspection of components, making it relevant to this sub-category.
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the level of security of components in a protocol, which can be analyzed using information-theoretic concepts, making it relevant to this sub-category.
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve analyzing the computational complexity of the protocol or the method used to analyze it, making it relevant to this sub-category.
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper may involve implementing the proposed method in software or analyzing the software engineering aspects of the protocol, making it relevant to this sub-category.
